default&#xa0;defaultRemunerationdefault68.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultNuffield Health has a Remuneration Committee, comprising trustees of the cha
defaultrity, which takes independent advice from external advisors. It ensures that senior executives and other employees receive the necessary development and leadership opportunities, and are appropriately motivated and rewarded for their individual and collect
defaultive contributions to the 
defaultorganisation’s
default overall performance. 
default69.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWith respect to executive remuneration, the Committee has delegated authority from Nuffield Health’s Board of Governors to determine the remuneration package for all senior executives including 
defaultthe Chief Executive.
default70.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultNuffield Health remuneration package: total compensation, including pension contributions, bonuses and other benefits, is positioned at 75% of the market median (median rate, discounted by 25%) for the reference market. [E.G. if there
default are 11 companies in the comparative market group for a role, and the total compensation level for each company is ranked from lowest to highest, the median level is that of the company positioned in the middle at 6th place. We benchmark at this point and 
defaultthen apply a further 25% discount to determine the level of remuneration].
default71.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCurrent reference market is a selection of companies based on comparable 
defaultorganisational
default size and complexity. 
default72.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCommittee informed of total compensation levels in private and public h
defaultealthcare 
defaultorganisations
default, and leading charities of a comparable size, to gauge relative positioning of executive packages. 
default73.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOur trustees conduct an independent annual review of executive remuneration and view the salaries of our executives as being at the a
defaultppropriate level to attract and retain the talent required to sustain the success of the charity. 
default74.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe believe that a charity should be transparent so all of our pay levels are published in our Annual Report and Accounts.
